TITLE: California’s Housing Crisis and the Fight Over 20 Townhomes
SUMMARY: Suburban homeowners like Susan Kirsch are often blamed for worsening the nation’s housing crisis. That doesn’t mean she’s giving up her two-decade fight against 20 condos.

TITLE: Hiring Remains Strong Even as Fed Tries to Cool Economy
SUMMARY: The Labor Department reported 390,000 new jobs in May, as policymakers try to ease inflation without inducing a recession.

TITLE: Is ‘Greedflation’ Rewriting Economics, or Do Old Rules Still Apply?
SUMMARY: Economists and politicians are debating whether monopolistic companies are fueling inflation in ways that confound longstanding theory.

TITLE: Ford Plans 6,000 New Union Jobs in Three Midwestern States
SUMMARY: The automaker said the move would further its electric-vehicle goals. It may also defuse tensions with the U.A.W. ahead of contract talks next year.

TITLE: U.S. Technology, a Longtime Tool for Russia, Becomes a Vulnerability
SUMMARY: Global restrictions on sending advanced technology to Russia are hampering the country’s military capacity, U.S. officials say, though Russia has stockpiled American equipment for years.

TITLE: Fed Vice Chair Says Another Big Interest Rate Increase Could Come in September
SUMMARY: Lael Brainard, the vice chair of the Federal Reserve, said another big rate increase in September might be appropriate if inflation did not moderate.

TITLE: Why a Not-So-Hot Economy Might Be Good News
SUMMARY: As the Federal Reserve tries to rein in inflation without causing a recession, slower job creation and wage growth could be a plus.

TITLE: Job Openings Declined Slightly in April From a High Point
SUMMARY: Employers had 11.4 million vacancies, nearly two for every worker seeking a job.

TITLE: Biden Administration Begins Trade Dialogue With Taiwan
SUMMARY: Talks with the self-governing island, which China claims as its territory, aim to challenge Chinese trade practices and are sure to irritate Beijing.

TITLE: Seizing Russian Assets to Help Ukraine Sets Off White House Debate
SUMMARY: Some European officials want to use more than $300 billion in Russian central bank assets to rebuild Ukraine. But Biden administration officials warn that diverting those funds could be illegal.

TITLE: N.Y.C. Companies Are Opening Offices Where Their Workers Live: Brooklyn
SUMMARY: As workers return to the office, some companies have relocated to ease the commute.

TITLE: Illegal Immigration Is Down, Changing the Face of California Farms
SUMMARY: Farmers are turning to workers on seasonal visas and mechanizing what they can. Many labor-intensive crops are shifting south of the border.

TITLE: Pakistan Raises Fuel Prices in Effort to Stabilize Economy
SUMMARY: The interim government’s move was seen as a bid to revive a $6 billion bailout from the International Monetary Fund.

TITLE: Americans Keep Spending Even as Inflation Erodes Buying Power
SUMMARY: To keep up with rising prices, Americans are saving less, but economists expect expenditures to slow in the months ahead.

TITLE: E. Gerald Corrigan, Who Helped Ease ’87 Stock Crash, Dies at 80
SUMMARY: As president of the Federal Reserve Bank of New York, he favored flooding the financial system with cash to restore confidence among investors.

TITLE: Fed Minutes Show Officials Expecting to Raise Rates Three Times to Address Inflation
SUMMARY: Minutes of the Federal Reserve’s May meeting underscored the deep concern within the central bank about rapidly rising prices that have far exceeded the Fed’s target.

TITLE: U.S. Will Start Blocking Russia’s Bond Payments to American Investors
SUMMARY: The Biden administration’s escalation of sanctions could lead to Russia’s first default on foreign debt in a century.

TITLE: Debate Over Tariffs Reveals Biden’s Difficulties on China Trade
SUMMARY: Sixteen months into the Biden presidency, U.S. officials are still divided over what to do about a trade legacy left by President Donald J. Trump.

TITLE: Baby Formula Shortage Has an Aggravating Factor: Few Producers
SUMMARY: With just a handful of companies making U.S. infant formula, a shutdown of Abbott’s plant had outsized impact on the supply.

TITLE: Big Tech Is Getting Clobbered on Wall Street. It’s a Good Time for Them.
SUMMARY: Flush with cash, Facebook, Apple, Amazon, Microsoft and Google are positioned to emerge from a downturn stronger and more powerful. As usual.
